    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Transfers the callback stack to a fresh ExitStack instance and returns it. No callbacks are invoked by this operation - instead, they will now be invoked when the new stack is closed (either explicitly or implicitly at the end of a with statement). For example, a group of files can be opened as an “all or nothing” operation as follows: with ExitStack() as stack: files = [stack.enter_context(open(fname)) for fname in filenames] # Hold onto the close method, but don't call it yet. close_files =..."
